etymology.description: 𠀠 (basket pictogram) + 丌 (stand or phonetic component) -> modified 𠔝 -> borrowed for pronoun "his"
etymology.interpretation: The character 丌 represents an ancient component originally depicting a stand added beneath a basket. Over time, this component became associated with the character 其(其) (qí, "his"), where 丌 contributed both to the meaning of a stand and possibly functioned as a phonetic component.
